The appropriateness of Teucer’s honoring Hercules at this time lies in the character of Hercules as a traveler (3, 3, 9 vagus Her- cules) and leader (Xen. Anah.. 4, 8, 25 ἡγεμών), to whose pro— tection Teucer might naturally in- trust himself when starting on this uncertain journey. Furthermore it was in company with Hercules that Telamon took Troy (cf. Verg. A. 1, 619 ff.) and captured Hesione, who became Teucer's mother.
